New Records: Rookie Tristan da Silva scored a career-best 25 points.
Key Match Events: Tristan da Silva was 5-for-7 on 3-point attempts.
Orlando Magic defeated the Toronto Raptors 106-97.
Goga Bitadze had 11 points, 13 rebounds, and seven assists.
Cole Anthony contributed nine points and 11 assists off the bench.
Jalen Suggs left the game with back spasms late in the second quarter.
Orlando made 19 3-pointers to control the game.
Jakob Poeltl scored 25 points for the Raptors.
Scottie Barnes added 20 points and nine rebounds.
Immanuel Quickley had 11 points and 11 assists.
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Mose commented that Tristan da Silva is not getting enough recognition as a rookie.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Toronto's RJ Barrett (illness) and Orlando's Anthony Black (back) did not play.
